<li id="comment-5549" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
<div class="comment-author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/568be784a48b187e9c860b701c18c3fa?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=G' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span class="fn n">Leonor Bosman</span></div>
<div class="comment-meta">Posted February 9, 2015 at 3:41 pm <span class="meta-sep"> | </span> <a href="#comment-5549" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div>
<div class="comment-content">
<p>Snoeters: dalk weet jy dit nie maar daar is eintlik twee laers onder die afrikanerboer en  Boer. Die klomp wat Calvinisties is en Jesus as God aanbid en hom aanroep vir verlossing want hy is mos die verlosser.</p>
<p>Dan is daar die laer van Yahweh wat die Boer se Verlosser is. Bly in jou laer en ons sal in ons laer bly. Ek verseker jou jy hoef Dirk uit te jaag nie want hy is nie in julle laer nie. Ons God Yahweh is ‘n Kryger (Exo 15:3) en Hy soek baie Rambos nie papperige liefdevolle christene nie. </p>
<p>Israel is die volk van Yahweh vir wie Hy Sy Torah gegee het en met die einste volk sal Hy koninkryke en laers vernietig.  Yahweh beveel ons om Hom by Sy Naam te noem en Hyself noem Hom  min of meer 87 keer die God van Israel  en sowat 29 keer die God of Magtige van Jakob.</p>
<p>Let there be no doubt about this, Yahweh is a God of peace to those who LOVE AND OBEY Him. However, to the wicked who try to overthrow all His rule in this world, He is a man of war, as Exodus 15:3 states. Psalm 24:8 reminds us, &#8220;Who is this King of glory? Yahweh strong and mighty, Yahweh mighty in battle.&#8221; In Psalm 18:32,34,&amp; 39 David says, &#8220;It is Yahweh that girdeth me with strength, and maketh my way perfect. He teacheth my hands to war, so that a bow of steel is broken by my arms. For Thou hast girded me with strength unto the battle: Thou hast subdued under me those that rose up against me.&#8221;<br />
In Jeremiah 51:20 Yahweh gives us our orders saying, &#8220;Thou(Israel) art My battle axe and WEAPONS OF WAR (jy weet die Rambos): for with thee will I destroy kingdoms.&#8221;</p>
</div>
