<li id="comment-5670" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
<div class="comment-author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/8524889c776056dce6484a1192b75bbf?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=G' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span class="fn n">Marellus</span></div>
<div class="comment-meta">Posted February 13, 2015 at 5:24 pm <span class="meta-sep"> | </span> <a href="#comment-5670" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div>
<div class="comment-content">
<p>Leonor,</p>
<p>Weet jy ooit wie Julius Firmicus Maternus is ?</p>
<p>Hy was &#8216;n Christelike skrywer wat in die vierde eeu n.C (d.i 300-399 n.C) geleef het. </p>
<p>Hy het twee groot boeke skrywe nl. een wat handel oor Astrologie, en toe bekeer hy homself, en skrywe die volgende boek :</p>
<p>&#8220;De Errore Profanarum Religionum&#8221; wat beteken &#8220;The Profane Errors of Religion&#8221; </p>
<p>Ek haal nou daaruit aan:</p>
<p>&#8220;The woman they represent with three faces and girded with huge snakes&#8230; while in the worship of the hero who drove off the bulls they transfer his rites to the cult of the fire, as his poet has recorded for us when he wrote:</p>
<p>    &#8220;Mystic priest of the captured bulls, skilful son of a noble sire.&#8221;</p>
<p>To him they give the name Mithras, and celebrate his rites in secret caves, that shrouded in the dim obscurityof the darkness they may shun the touch of the pure and glorious light. </p>
<p>Truly an ill-omened exaltation of a deity! a hateful recognition of a barbarian rite! to deify one whose criminal acts your confess.&#8221; </p>
<p>Hier is jou Mithra-geloof, (wat is jóú bron in elk geval ?) en jy sê die Christelike geloof stam hiervan af ?</p>
<p>Belaglik.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.thedyinggod.com/chaldeanmagi/Firmicus-Maternus" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-comment', 'http://www.thedyinggod.com/chaldeanmagi/Firmicus-Maternus', 'http://www.thedyinggod.com/chaldeanmagi/Firmicus-Maternus']);"  rel="nofollow">http://www.thedyinggod.com/chaldeanmagi/Firmicus-Maternus</a></p>
</div>
<ul class="children">
<li id="comment-5677" class="comment odd alt depth-2">
<div class="comment-author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/568be784a48b187e9c860b701c18c3fa?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=G' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span class="fn n">Leonor Bosman</span></div>
<div class="comment-meta">Posted February 14, 2015 at 2:08 pm <span class="meta-sep"> | </span> <a href="#comment-5677" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div>
<div class="comment-content">
<p>Marellus<br />
Maternus was ‘n roomse katolieke ‘christen’. So sal niks wat hy sê in ag neem nie.<br />
<a href="http://www.astrologiahumana.com/firmicusmaternustheoryandpractice.pdf" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','download','http://www.astrologiahumana.com/firmicusmaternustheoryandpractice.pdf']);"  rel="nofollow">http://www.astrologiahumana.com/firmicusmaternustheoryandpractice.pdf</a><br />
Heiden.</p>
<p>Mitrahism religion, mystery and secrecy,  Many facts discovered sheds vital light on the cultural dynamics that led to the rise of Christianity.  The National Geographic Society’s book “Great Religions of the World,” page 309 writes; “By Jesus’ time, East and West had mingled here for three centuries.  Down columns of boulevards walked Roman soldiers loyal to the Persian god Mithras.” Mithras was a Persian deity.  He was also the most widely venerated god in the Roman Empire at the time of Jesus.<br />
<a href="http://jdstone.org/cr/files/mithraschristianity.html" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-comment', 'http://jdstone.org/cr/files/mithraschristianity.html', 'http://jdstone.org/cr/files/mithraschristianity.html']);"  rel="nofollow">http://jdstone.org/cr/files/mithraschristianity.html</a></p>
<p>Mithraism: Mithra was called the son of God, born of a virgin, had disciples, was crucified, rose from the dead on the 3rd day, atoned for the sins of mankind, and returned to heaven.</p>
</div>
<ul class="children">
<li id="comment-5678" class="comment even depth-3">
<div class="comment-author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/568be784a48b187e9c860b701c18c3fa?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=G' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span class="fn n">Leonor Bosman</span></div>
<div class="comment-meta">Posted February 14, 2015 at 2:11 pm <span class="meta-sep"> | </span> <a href="#comment-5678" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div>
<div class="comment-content">
<p>&#8220;although we know of no mystery-cult that reproduces exactly the same configuration as the [apostle Paul's] doctrine, we find in mystery-cult the ideas of the death and rebirth of the initiand (e.g. Apuleius Metamorphoses 11.21), of the sufferings of the deity (e.g. Athenagoras Supplication 32.1), of the identification of the initiand with deity, and of the initiands&#8217; (transition to) salvation depending on their finding &#8212; or the return to life of &#8212; a deity (e.g. Lactantius Divine Institutions 18.7; Firmucus Maternus On the Error of Profane Religions 2.9; 22.1-3)&#8230;.Dionysos, like Jesus, was the son of the divine ruler of the world and a mortal mother, appeared in human form among mortals, was killed and restored to life. Early Christian writers, aware of the similarity between Christianity and mystery-cult, claim that the latter is a DIABOLICAL IMITATION OF THE FORMER&#8230;.  (SEAFORD, PAGE 123-124, 126)</p>
<p>Ja right!</p>
<p>Voeg daarby Kerssongodfees en paashaasfees en bloed en brood en jy het die net nog &#8216;n heidense godsiens. Die christendom het hulle wortels in die heidense gelowe. Klaar.</p>
<p>Maw. Potyto potato.  Te veel te toevallig. En 16 sestien ander verlossers van die wêreld? Probeer weer.</p>
</div>
